cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SI 

This paper discusses the joint sponsored and edge caching content service market in wireless networks, which involves network infrastructure, content providers, and mobile users. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also uses game theory to model the interactions among the different stakeholders, which suggests the category cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also discusses information theory and optimization techniques, which suggests the categories cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the economic aspects of the sponsored content market, which suggests the category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
